    • Constructor Detail

      • TAG_BEXT

        public TAG_BEXT()
        Create an object that holds a null TAG_BEXT.
        The call isNull() on the object created will returns true.
          TAG_BEXT obj = new TAG_BEXT();
  (obj == null) <=> false
  obj.isNull() <=> true
        To creates a new TAG_BEXT, use the static "constructor" : 
          TAG_BEXT obj = TAG_BEXT.allocate();
        See Also:
        allocate()

    • Method Detail

      • asTAG_BEXT

        public static TAG_BEXT asTAG_BEXT(Pointer pointer)
        Create a view of the Pointer object as a TAG_BEXT object.
        This view is valid only if the memory holded by the Pointer holds a TAG_BEXT object.

      • allocate

        public static TAG_BEXT allocate()
        Allocate a new TAG_BEXT.
